<small>You are running a beta release of postmarketOS. Install updates now and make regular backups of important data. Please read the following information carefully.</small>
 
<b>Open/close the top menu:</b> tap the top bar between clock and battery. Tap again in the same spot to close it. <small>(It will likely become more intuitive, see phosh#143).</small>

<b>Connect to Wi-Fi:</b> open the top menu, tap the Wi-Fi icon. Be patient, the load indication is missing.
 
<b>Install updates:</b> tap the bottom arrow, scroll down to <i>Software</i>. Select <i>Updates</i> on the bottom right. Update now and periodically to receive latest fixes and improvements.

<b>Lockscreen / power off:</b> open the top menu, tap the power symbol on the top right.

<b>Close this app (and others):</b> tap the bottom arrow, swipe the preview screen for this app upwards.

Find detailed usage instructions in the wiki:
<a href="https://postmarketos.org/intro-phosh">https://postmarketos.org/intro-phosh</a>
If something is not working, report it here:
<a href="https://postmarketos.org/issues">https://postmarketos.org/issues</a>

<small>Thanks to everybody who contributed to postmarketOS or upstream projects - Alpine, Phosh, Linux kernel and many more! As Linux enthusiast, <i>you</i> can contribute to postmarketOS too: package build recipes are simple shell scripts. Our development and install tool pmbootstrap gets you started in a few minutes on <i>any</i> Linux distribution.</small>
